cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.PE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with user positioning in 5G networks using beamforming techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a two-stage extended Kalman filter for accurate positioning and tracking of users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with millimeter wave (mmW) band, which is used for high-speed multimedia applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper proposes a scalable positioning scheme that shares the computational burden among different network entities. 
- cs.PE (Performance) is another possible category as the paper assesses the performance of the proposed algorithm on a realistic outdoor 5G deployment with a detailed ray tracing propagation model.
